## Applied (safe, surgical)
1. proposal-writer.md dash gate: grep referenced a hard-coded `cover-letter.md` but the real file is `cover-letter.txt`, so the CEO-caught em dash in the cover-letter title line slipped past. Changed to glob the ACTUAL files by extension and to explicitly cover the first line / `<title>` / header, not just body. Directly addresses the final-ceo hard-gate fail root cause.
2. deploy-test.md: added a note that demo input fields are often blank on load and a Run/Submit handler can return early and silently no-op when empty; the hero flow must fill required inputs first, then assert real output. (from improvements.md deploy-test [adherence]).

